The paper discusses the profiling and characterization of machine learning models, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus is on optimizing the computing system for ML models, which involves hardware and system design, making it relevant to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions GPU hardware, which is commonly used in computer graphics and augmented reality (cs.AR). Additionally, the paper discusses the behavior of ML models in different application domains, including computer vision (cs.CV) and deep learning (cs.LG).
